    12000: "A large fan decorated with glittering stars.",
    12001: "Savvy Socialite Control Bar",
    12002: "Savvy Socialite Knuckles",
    12003: "A Control Bar with bejeweled accents.\nEven the time-honored traditions of puppetry can benefit from a touch of luxury.",
    12004: "Knuckles studded with jewels of high hardness, designed to hit like (literally) a rock. The ornate metal has been treated so it won't tarnish over time.",
    12005: "Planet Lantern",
    12006: "A beautiful planet-themed lantern that glows even brighter at night.",
    12007: "Crescent Sword",
    12008: "Planet Chain Blade",
    12009: "A one-handed sword in the shape of a crescent. It may be fancy, but it's still deadly sharp.",
    12010: "A chain blade shaped like a morningstar with planets attached to it. The large planet at the end is sharpened for extra destruction.",
    12011: "Demolition Breaker Bow",
    12012: "Bow of Ruination",
    12013: "Demolition Deepglow Staff",
    12014: "Lord of Ruination Staff",
    12015: "Demolition Breaker Arrows",
    12016: "Arrows of Ruination",
    12017: "A bow infused with the power to demolish whatever its arrows hit. Possessing excessive power in comparison to conventional bows, one would do well to show care in handling it.",
    12018: "A bow made from refined minerals that emanate a strange and ominous energy. The act of drawing the bow also draws out that latent might, enabling a level of force far greater than its physical parameters would suggest.",
    12019: "A staff imbued with the power to amplify magic, laying waste to all its wielder wishes to destroy. Possessing far greater power than most staves, one would do well to show care in its handling. It has the power to call on all magic skills of the three elements and, when held, allows you to use the Meditation skill while running.",
    12020: "A reforging tool capable of simple work, used to grant new attributes to equipment. <color=2>Cannot be used on equipment that has already been reforged.</color>",
    12021: "Special arrows infused with the power to demolish whatever they hit.\n(Can be dyed)",
    12022: "Special arrows made from refined minerals that emanate a strange and ominous energy.\n(Can be dyed)",
    12023: "Dreamseer's Unicorn Horn",
    12024: "An event voucher earned by answering correctly in the OX Quiz or completing related quests. You can take them to Locke to exchange for a variety of rewards.\n* Any remaining vouchers will disappear one week after the event has ended.",
    12025: "A coin for checking OX Quiz Event goal achievements. Cannot be used to purchase special items from the shop.",
    12026: "Lovers Ring",
    12027: "Engagement Ring",
    12028: "Wedding Ring",
    12029: "Variscite (Not tradable)",
    12030: "Orpiment (Not tradable)",
    12031: "A memory from a moment of triumphant glory that has manifested in a crystalline form.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12032: "A crest that pulses with the mysterious energy of Bri Leith.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12033: "A piece of a blade that has grown worn and dull with the passage of time. With a good sharpening, it could still prove useful.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12034: "A highly pliable metal fragment able to easily fuse with other materials.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12035: "Threads taken from a once-beautiful embroidered work. Looking at it recalls memories of a bygone time.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12036: "A Mana Stone whose energy has been completely exhausted. Emptied of its mana, it can be used as a receptacle for other types of energy.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12037: "A crystalline carbonate mineral with a cloudy translucency.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12038: "An aluminum phosphate mineral prized for its intense green color.\n\nCan be used as a crafting material.\n(Not tradable)",
    12039: "Omamori Amulet",
