    13084: "Perseus Forbidden Spell Book",
    13085: "A bow containing a fragment of a great power that has crystallized over the course of eons. An aura of darkness emanates from it like a stormcloud.",
    13086: "A wand containing a fragment of a great power that has crystallized over the course of eons. An aura of darkness emanates from it like a stormcloud.",
    13087: "A greataxe fashioned from a restored battle axe said to have been wielded by a goddess. Its broad, sharp double blades strike with unyielding force, inflicting great damage on foes. Despite its hulking size, both humans and Elves can wield it.",
    13088: "A greataxe fashioned in the likeness of one possessed by a goddess. Its broad, curved edge can cleave through the toughest targets. Despite its hulking size, both humans and Elves can wield it.",
    13089: "A staff born of the will of a goddess. Those who upgrade it will find themselves able to more effectively regulate their mana. It has the power to call on all magic skills of the three elements and, when held, allows you to use the Meditation skill while running.",
    13090: "A staff that reflects the generosity of a goddess, enabling the wielder to cast powerful magic attacks or support allies with the Party Healing skill. It has the power to call on all magic skills of the three elements and, when held, allows you to use the Meditation skill while running.",
    13091: "A lance fashioned in the likeness of one possessed by a goddess. It has been imbued with an ancient power that resounds in the clangor of its blows.",
    13092: "Frozen Heart Gloves (M)",
    13093: "Dark Riftbreakers",
    13094: "A cylinder that Taise uses. According to Taise, it can wiggle-giggle elemental energy to do some impressive bubble-trouble.",
    13095: "A matched pair of handguns wielded by Micheil. Apparently, the name was inspired by the vacuum created by bullets as they travel through the air. He probably wouldn't answer if you tried to ask him for a more detailed explanation.",
    13096: "Festive Eastern Lantern Staff",
    13097: "A staff whose design takes inspiration from the rows of hanging lanterns that illuminate thoroughfares and pathways during festivals. Carrying it, you feel as though you could lead a mysterious procession.",
