    16000: "Leather Gloves",
    16001: "A large teddy bear that's totally hip with it. Or so it thinks, with its head full of neon fluff. When you take it with you on your adventures, you feel as though you're sliding through a candy-colored dreamscape.",
    16002: "Lightning Staff",
    16003: "A special staff presented to Royal Mages who have been recognized for distinguished service to the kingdom. It has the power to call on all magic skills of the three elements and, when held, allows you to use the Meditation skill while running.",
    16004: "Cherished Bunny Doll",
    16005: "Charming Bunny Doll",
    16006: "Cherished Little Miss Doll",
    16007: "Cherished Teddy Bear",
    16008: "Charming Teddy Bear",
    16009: "Beloved Teddy Bear",
    16010: "Beloved Bunny Doll",
    16011: "This floppy-eared bunny doll stirs feelings of warmth and fondness in those who hold it. Though timid at heart, it will gladly accompany you on your journeys.",
    16012: "This floppy-eared bunny doll stirs feelings of warmth and fondness in those who hold it. Though timid at heart, it will gladly accompany you on your journeys.",
    16013: "This cute doll is a veteran of many a tea party and is acquainted with more than a few princesses. In spite of her prim and proper appearance, she welcomes your affection and will gladly accompany you on your journeys.",
    16014: "This teddy bear stirs feelings of warmth and caring in those who hold it. It seems to welcome big hugs, and will gladly accompany you on your journeys.",
    16015: "This teddy bear stirs feelings of warmth and caring in those who hold it. It seems to welcome big hugs, and will gladly accompany you on your journeys.",
    16016: "A well-loved teddy bear from your childhood. Though your adventures together have left it a bit threadbare in places, thinking of those heartfelt times makes its presence all the more comforting.",
    16017: "A well-loved bunny doll from your childhood. Though your adventures together have left it a bit threadbare in places, thinking of those heartfelt times makes its presence all the more comforting.",
    16018: "Moonlight Hunter's Silvered Blade",
    16019: "Moonlight Hunter's Crossbow",
    16020: "Moonlight Hunter's Dread Cleaver",
    16021: "@Claus' Leather Gloves",
    16022: "Tiger Paw",
    16023: "Elysees Maid Gloves (F)",
    16024: "An outfit worn by those who wander the forests, sworn to protect the wildlands. Fashioned from durable cloth and sturdy leather, it allows the wearer to move through woods and fields unseen by most.",
    16025: "신비한 비밀을 간직한 화원에 등장하는 소녀에게 어울릴 것 같은 가발이다. 부드럽게 떨어지는 웨이브의 우아함 속에 세련미를 함께 느낄 수 있다.",
    16026: "신비한 비밀을 간직한 화원에 등장하는 소녀에게 어울릴 것 같은 가발이다. 부드럽게 떨어지는 웨이브의 우아함과 플라워 밴드의 매치가 신비함을 더해준다.",
    16027: "Mittens made to keep winter's cold at bay. With their warm fur lining, your hands will stay toasty no matter how many snowballs you pack and throw.",
    16028: "Eochaid Figure",
    16029: "Homestead Lazy Purrling Figure",
    16030: "Homestead Sled Team Husky Figure",
    16031: "Homestead Marathon Camel Figure",
    16032: "Homestead Adventurous Elephant Figure",
    16033: "Place this Lazy Purrling Figure on your Homestead for a little boost to your stats.\n*Luck: +10, Movement Speed: +1%\nThis item's effects can stack with the effects from Sequel Figures, but not from other regular Figures. (The stat increase will disappear if this item is removed from the Homestead.)\nPlace the entire Commerce Animal set and the Lazy Purrling Figure on your Homestead for a special bonus.\n(The set effect cannot stack with the effects from Figures.)",
    16034: "Place this Sled Team Husky Figure on your Homestead for a little boost to your stats.\n*Dexterity: +10, Max MP: +30\nThis item's effects can stack with the effects from Sequel Figures, but not from other regular Figures. (The stat increase will disappear if this item is removed from the Homestead.)\nPlace the entire Commerce Animal set and the Lazy Purrling Figure on your Homestead for a special bonus.\n(The set effect cannot stack with the effects from Figures.)",
    16035: "Place this Marathon Camel Figure on your Homestead for a little boost to your stats.\n*Will: +10, Max Stamina: +30\nThis item's effects can stack with the effects from Sequel Figures, but not from other regular Figures. (The stat increase will disappear if this item is removed from the Homestead.)\nPlace the entire Commerce Animal set and the Lazy Purrling Figure on your Homestead for a special bonus.\n(The set effect cannot stack with the effects from Figures.)",
    16036: "Place this Aura figure in your Homestead for a little boost to your stats.\n[*Luck: +2]\n(Effects cannot be stacked. Stat increase will disappear if taken down.)",
    16037: "밤의 서약 상자",
    16038: "A scroll that changes a weapon's appearance to that of the Royal Society Scythe. You can only use it on a Scythe. (Cannot be used on Classic Spirit Weapons or other select weapons.) The scroll will disappear once the effect has been applied.",
    16039: "Place this Frieren figure in your Homestead for a little boost to your stats.\n[*Strength: +2]\n(Effects cannot be stacked. Stat increase will disappear if taken down.)",
    16040: "Hard Mode Rundal Advanced Fomor Pass (Party of 2)",
    16041: "This is a special Fomor pass.\nPlace it on the Rundal Dungeon Old Room altar to enter the Hard Mode Rundal Advanced Fomor Dungeon.\nParty size: 2\n(Not tradable)",
    16042: "Pure Fused Shyllien",
