    16501: "Moonlight Hunter's Chain Blade",
    16502: "A one-handed sword tempered with pure silver, used by Moonlight Hunters in their battles against the servants of darkness. It seems to exude an air of nobility.",
    16503: "A powerful crossbow capable of loosing envenomed or silver-tipped bolts, used by Moonlight Hunters in their battles against the servants of darkness. It seems to exude an air of prudence.",
    16504: "배쉬 이펙트 변경 카드(루미나 퓨어 스페이스)",
    16505: "A large pair of dual guns that can loose bullets with enough force to stop even frenzied beasts in their tracks, used by Moonlight Hunters in their battles against the servants of darkness. They seem to exude an air of remorselessness.",
    16506: "A blackened chain blade that can lash foes while remaining out of range of their teeth and claws, used by Moonlight Hunters in their battles against the servants of darkness. It seems to exude an air of temperance.",
    16507: "Brielle's Bag",
    16508: "A bag like the one Brielle carries as she travels around Erinn. She claims it also makes a serviceable bludgeon in a pinch.",
    16509: "@Spika's Silver Gauntlet",
    16510: "Virtuous Dreamseer's Unicorn Halo",
    16511: "@Silver Teany Glove",
    16512: "Blessed Ornament Shuriken",
    16513: "An atlatl that was molded into a festive shape. It may look cute but the tip is still sharp.",
    16514: "Virtuous Dreamseer's Unicorn Wings",
    16515: "A lance decorated with cute ornaments. It has been granted special powers and shines with a sacred light.\n\nWhile lances excel at attacking enemies at a distance, only those who have truly mastered the art of lance combat can use them at close range.",
    16516: "A shuriken that is reminiscent of a snowflake. It's decorated with a cute ribbon and the blades shine with a sacred light.",
    16517: "A halo inspired by the noble nature of a unicorn. Its sparkling effect lends it a dreamlike look.",
    16518: "A halo inspired by the noble nature of a unicorn. Its sparkling effect lends it a dreamlike look.",
    16519: "Blessed Ornament Cylinder",
    16520: "Seraphic Cantabile Wig (M)",
    16521: "Seraphic Cantabile Wig (F)",
    16522: "A wig styled in a neat and reserved fashion. It conveys both an abiding warmth and a resolute faith.",
    16523: "Moonshadow Emissary's Bracelets (M) (Rental)",
    16524: "Etching this signet onto your Divine Spell Book will amplify its power. It can be used on a Divine Spell Book with level 5 or higher Signet Effect to level up its Signet Effect by 1.",
    16525: "신께 기도하며 경건하게 손질한 가발. 고위급 대사제들의 헤어스타일이다. 깊은 신앙심의 고결함이 느껴진다.",
    16526: "Only those who have surpassed limitations to awaken a mighty defensive power can utilize this heavy armor to its full potential. The reinforced Geas in this item enhances your Techniques.",
    16527: "야성의 기운이 물씬 느껴지는 강렬한 프린트의 여성 수영복",
    16528: "@Razor Gauntlet",
    16529: "Two-handed Sword Stance Card (Type 2) (60 Days)",
    16530: "A bottle containing a strange energy distilled during research of the kingdom's scholarly Royal Societies, which becomes available as an appearance for your Stardust when you use this item.",
    16531: "A scroll that changes a weapon's appearance to that of a Noble Golf Club. You can only use it on a two-handed axe. (Cannot be used on Classic Spirit Weapons or other select weapons.) The scroll will disappear once the effect has been applied.",
    16532: "Doki Doki Kid Doll (Max Stamina Totem)",
    16533: "Doki Doki Paintbrush Doll (Defense/Magic Defense Totem)",
    16534: "A card that changes the visual effect of the Death Mark skill. Right-click and select 'Activate' to turn on the Angry Cute Bear effect. Each character can only possess one such effect-altering card.",
    16535: "A Reforging Tool capable of detailed work, used to grant new attributes to equipment. These tools grant a random set of new attributes each time they are used, so if your equipment already possesses Reforging attributes, you will need to consider whether to keep your current bonuses or try for a better combination of attributes.",
    16536: "썬더 스킬을 사용했을 때 이펙트가 달라지는 카드. 마우스 오른쪽 버튼 클릭 후 '활성화'를 선택하면 퓨어 화이트 일렉트릭 테크 외형의 이펙트를 확인할 수 있다. 이펙트 변경 카드는 캐릭터 당 1개만 가질 수 있다.",
