    20032: "특별한 손수건을 사용하여 특별한 코인을 획득했다. 모아둔 코인으로 여러가지 아이템을 교환할 수 있다.",
    20033: "특별한 손수건을 사용하여 특별한 코인을 획득했다. 모아둔 코인으로 여러가지 아이템을 교환할 수 있다.",
    20034: "특별한 손수건을 사용하여 특별한 코인을 획득했다. 모아둔 코인으로 여러가지 아이템을 교환할 수 있다.",
    20035: "Homestead Masterpiece Scene Vol. 3",
    20036: "Homestead Masterpiece Scene Vol. 4",
    20037: "Vol. 3 in a series of inspiring reproductions of memorable scenes. Place it on your Homestead to relive the three lost warriors' legendary fight.",
    20038: "Vol. 4 in a series of inspiring reproductions of memorable scenes. Place it on your Homestead to relive Succubus Kristell's fateful encounter with Tarlach.",
    20039: "Hard Mode Ciar Advanced Fomor Pass (Event)",
    20040: "Hard Mode Alby Advanced Fomor Pass (Event)",
    20041: "Hard Mode Rundal Advanced Fomor Pass (Event)",
    20042: "<color=1>This item can no longer be used after the November 13, 2025 update. However, you can exchange it for a Neartite crystal by speaking with Soraia at the Poulnabrone research site.</color>\n\nThis is a special Fomor pass. Place it on the altar at the entrance of the Ciar Dungeon to enter the Ciar Advanced Hard Mode Dungeon.\n\n(Not tradable)",
    20043: "<color=1>This item can no longer be used after the November 13, 2025 update. However, you can exchange it for a Neartite crystal by speaking with Soraia at the Poulnabrone research site.</color>\n\nThis is a special Fomor pass. Place it on the altar at the entrance of the Alby Dungeon to enter the Alby Advanced Hard Mode Dungeon.\n\n(Not tradable)",
    20044: "<color=1>This item can no longer be used after the November 13, 2025 update. However, you can exchange it for a Neartite crystal by speaking with Soraia at the Poulnabrone research site.</color>\n\nThis is a special Fomor pass. Place it on the altar at the entrance of the Rundal Dungeon to enter the Rundal Advanced Hard Mode Dungeon.\n\n(Not tradable)",
    20045: "Alchemic Power Potion (30 min.)",
    20046: "Alchemic Power Potion (2 hrs.)",
    20047: "Light Alchemic Power Potion (30 min.)",
    20048: "Light Alchemic Power Potion (2 hrs.)",
    20049: "A potion that increases Alchemic Damage by 20% for 30 minutes.",
    20050: "A potion that increases Alchemic Damage by 20% for 2 hours.",
    20051: "Spirit Transformation Liqueur (Galvanic Charge)",
    20052: "Hospital Visit",
    20053: "Homunculus Incubator - Type Alpha (for 2)",
    20054: "Homunculus Incubator - Type Beta (for 2)",
    20055: "Homunculus Incubator - Type Gamma (for 2)",
    20056: "Homunculus Incubator - Type Delta (for 2)",
    20057: "A Storm Outside the Window",
    20058: "A Hall of Thunder that can be placed on your Homestead.\nFramed by an ancient-looking arch and braziers, a perpetual storm cloud sends lightning forking down in a mesmerizing display.",
    20059: "A scroll that changes a weapon's appearance to that of a Syringe Lance. You can only use it on a lance. (Cannot be used on Classic Spirit Weapons or other select weapons.) The scroll will disappear once the effect has been applied.",
    20060: "A liqueur said to have been brewed in the wildlands by shamans, imbued with the indomitable spirit of a ferocious beast. Use it to apply a Bestial Howl effect to your weapon. Because this is a special effect, it does not grant a size or color change based on the Spirit's level. Critical effects start at Spirit level 1.",
    20061: "A liqueur manufactured via a process that bombards the solution with energized particles, giving it a permanent charge. Use it to apply a Galvanic Charge effect to your weapon. Because this is a special effect, it does not grant a size or color change based on the Spirit's level. Critical effects start at Spirit level 1.",
    20062: "A scene of a hospital waiting with patients awaiting treatment. Take a rest leaning on an oversized syringe--that'll surely put everyone at ease!",
    20063: "A large vessel designed to foster the growth of homunculi in a variety of different environments. It provides a clear view to facilitate scientific observation.\n\nSeats up to 2 people.",
    20064: "A large vessel designed to foster the growth of homunculi in a variety of different environments. It provides a clear view to facilitate scientific observation.\n\nSeats up to 2 people.",
    20065: "A large vessel designed to foster the growth of homunculi in a variety of different environments. It provides a clear view to facilitate scientific observation.\n\nSeats up to 2 people.",
    20066: "A large vessel designed to foster the growth of homunculi in a variety of different environments. It provides a clear view to facilitate scientific observation.\n\nSeats up to 2 people.",
    20067: "Rest in comfort as you watch a thunderstorm rage outside from the warm, dry vantage of the nook beneath this stately window.",
    20068: "Leaf Coin",
    20069: "Special coins earned by participating in the Critter Cuteness Club event. Take them to the Magician Imp to exchange for a variety of rewards.\n* This item will disappear when the event ends.",
    20070: "Rebirth Potion",
    21001: "A rebirth potion. If you drink this potion, you can rebirth immediately. This item cannot be traded.",
    21002: "Milletian Welcome Erinn Settlement Equipment Bag",
    21003: "A bag made to welcome all Milletians to Erinn. This bag has 150 cells (10x15) and can only hold equipment items.\nThis item cannot be traded.",
